<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-01-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Squiers</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-14"><hi rend="italic">January 14,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 319.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to former correspondence in
                            regard to the killing of E. A. Murray, I have to request that you will
                            ask the foreign office to advise you as to the result of the
                            investigation which Mr. Zaldo on November 9 last stated had been ordered
                            “to find out what responsibility there may be on the part of the police
                            on duty at the police headquarters of Puerto Principe.”</p>
                        <p>You will inform the Department of the result of your inquiry.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Loomis.</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>